| Methocarbamol 750mg| 30–60 min              | 1–2 hours            | 1–2 hours         | Drowsiness, dizziness, confusion      | Muscle relaxant; depresses CNS to reduce muscle spasm                      |
| Diazepam 5mg       | 15–45 min (oral)       | 1–2 hours            | 20–50 hours       | Dependence, sedation, falls, confusion| Benzodiazepine; enhances GABA effect, reduces muscle tone & anxiety        |
| Ketesse 25mg       | 30 min                 | 30–60 min            | 1–2 hours         | GI upset, ulcers, kidney issues       | NSAID; rapidly blocks prostaglandin synthesis (anti-inflammatory, analgesic)|
| Naproxen 250mg     | 45–60 min              | 2–4 hours            | 12–17 hours       | GI upset, ulcers, kidney/heart risk   | NSAID; blocks prostaglandin synthesis (anti-inflammatory, analgesic)        |
| Dicloflex 50mg     | 30–60 min              | 1–2 hours            | 1–2 hours         | GI upset, ulcers, heart/liver risk    | NSAID; blocks prostaglandins, reduces inflammation and pain                 |
| Brexin (piroxicam) | 30–60 min              | 2–3 hours            | 40–50 hours       | GI upset, ulcers, skin reactions      | NSAID (long-acting); blocks prostaglandins, used for persistent pain        |
